EXEC P_THEME_LIST(SEQ_TNO.NEXTVAL,'ADMIN','Cherry blossom getaways from foreign Seoul veterans','<div class="contentHEAD" style="margin: 0px; padding: 1em 0px 0px; text-align: center;"><h3 style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">A Cherry Blossoms Guidebook from<br><k style="border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(252, 184, 238);">Foreign Seoul Veterans</k></h3><br><br><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28235&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=2" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"><br><br><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;">Whenever April comes around, the pink tinge of the cherry blossom flowers proclaim Spring’s arrival. As the current circumstances have it, we may not be able to fully enjoy the cherry blossoms this year, but we can at least appreciate their beauty in full bloom indifferent areas around the city as captured below. May next year offer the chance to get outside and take in the cherry blossoms to our hearts’ content! This month our team of non-Korean, Seoul-based editors introduce you to unique hot spots where you can embrace the cherry blossoms to welcome in the Spring! You can think of it as a chance to discover something new from your friendly foreign neighbors in Seoul!</p><div class="horizen" style="margin: 4em 0px; padding: 0px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=22676&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="구분자" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div></div><div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: center;"><h3 class="hcw_tit" style="margin: 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(252, 184, 238); line-height: 1.3;">#1 Seoul National Cemetery<br><span style="display: block; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 10px;">- Editor: Chen (Taiwan / 5th year in Seoul)<img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28261&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; margin-bottom: 0px; max-width: 100%;"></span></h3><div class="imgbox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; width: 1000px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28236&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=2" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;">Located in Dongjak-gu of Seoul, the Seoul National Cemetery serves as the grounds for the brave souls that sacrificed their lives for their country and its people. Every Spring, the scenery of the grounds convey a sense of nobility that only the Seoul National Cemetery encapsulates amid the weeping cheery blossoms with draping branches that dip gracefully back toward the earth. This location offers some respite from typically crowded areas so that visitors can enjoy a quiet stroll alongside breathtakingly striking cherry blossoms!</p><div class="infobox" style="margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 1.5em; border-radius: 0.5em; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); font-size: 0.8em;"><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28253&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="주소 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Address:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>271-78, Dongjak-dong, Dongjak-gu, Seoul</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28259&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="지하철 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Subway:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Lines 4 &amp; 9, Dongjak Station, Exits 2 &amp; 4</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28260&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=2" alt="시간 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Hours:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Daily 06:00 - 18:00</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28258&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="전화 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Phone:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>02-748-0114</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28255&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="사이트 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Website:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><a href="http://www.snmb.mil.kr/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">http://www.snmb.mil.kr/</a></p></div><div class="horizen" style="margin: 4em 0px; padding: 0px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=22676&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="구분자" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div></div><div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: center;"><h3 class="hcw_tit" style="margin: 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(252, 184, 238); line-height: 1.3;">#2 Yanghwa-ro 6-gil<br><span style="display: block; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 10px;">- Editor: Olga (Russia / 7th year in Seoul)<img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28257&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; margin-bottom: 0px; max-width: 100%;"></span></h3><div class="imgbox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; width: 1000px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28237&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;">Nested in the nook of Hapjeong-dong, Mapo-gu, the street, Yanghwa-ro 6-gil, offers an extravagant view hidden away that captures beautiful Seoul cherry blossoms at peak bloom, emanating a soft pink vibrancy. Ongoers can enjoy the scenery while taking snapshots at their leisure without all the bustling crowds, while perhaps strolling over to the picturesque cafes and eateries nearby!</p><div class="infobox" style="margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 1.5em; border-radius: 0.5em; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); font-size: 0.8em;"><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28253&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="주소 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Address:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Yanghwa-ro 6-gil, Mapo-gu, Seoul</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28259&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="지하철 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Subway:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Lines 2 &amp; 6, Hapjeong Station, Exit 5</p></div><div class="horizen" style="margin: 4em 0px; padding: 0px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=22676&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="구분자" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div></div><div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: center;"><h3 class="hcw_tit" style="margin: 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(252, 184, 238); line-height: 1.3;">#3 Children’s Grand Park<br><span style="display: block; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 10px;">- Editor: Ariel (China / 10th year in Seoul)<img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28254&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; margin-bottom: 0px; max-width: 100%;"></span></h3><div class="imgbox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; width: 1000px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28238&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;">Home to Gwangjin-gu while carrying with it a long history that lives in memory, the Children’s Grand Park is a go-to course among Seoulites, not just on Children’s Day, but on any day of the week, bringing in a number of couples and families alike. In fact,didyou know that the park has actually been long known for its cherry blossoms? With its widely-admired cherry blossoms since days of old, seasoned cherry trees uniformly line the Children’s Grand Park. Come on by and enjoy a stroll through the cherry blossom road running through the park’s entirety while taking in the colorful forsythias and various flowers tucked between the cherry trees. Feel free to let yourself be transported back to your childhood amid the wonder of the park zoo and botanical garden!</p><div class="infobox" style="margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 1.5em; border-radius: 0.5em; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); font-size: 0.8em;"><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28253&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="주소 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Address:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>216, Neungdong-ro, Gwangjin-gu, Seoul</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28259&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="지하철 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Subway:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Line 7, Children’s Grand Park Station, Exit 1</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28260&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=2" alt="시간 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Hours:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Daily 05:00 - 22:00</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28258&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="전화 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Phone:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>02-450-9311</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28255&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="사이트 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Website:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><a href="http://english.visitseoul.net/nature/Cherry-Blossom-Getaways-from-Foreign-Seoul-Veterans_/www.sisul.or.kr/open_content/childrenpark/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">http://sisul.or.kr/open_content/childrenpark/</a></p></div><div class="horizen" style="margin: 4em 0px; padding: 0px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=22676&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="구분자" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div></div><div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: center;"><h3 class="hcw_tit" style="margin: 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(252, 184, 238); line-height: 1.3;">#4 Donggyo-ro 41-gil<br><span style="display: block; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 10px;">- Editor: Rocky (U.S. / 15th year in Seoul)<img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28262&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; margin-bottom: 0px; max-width: 100%;"></span></h3><div class="imgbox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; width: 1000px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28239&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;">Upon sight, these rapturous flowers are sure to win your heart over after the long, cold Winter. It may commonplace to associate cherry blossoms with Yeouido, but we all know that when it comes down to it, after a visit to Yeouido, the only thing we get ourfill of are the massive crowds. That is why I am here to let you in on a little secret where you can be whisked away from all the noise to bask in the blooming cherry blossoms in peace! Yeonnam-dong is primarily known for being home to “Yeontral Park” (coined from New York’s “Central Park”), but tucked away within the cozy, neighborhood villa complexes, is, wouldn’t you know it, a road of cherry blossoms! Visitors can even enjoy little cafes, popular restaurants, famous filming sites, and much more, not only along the road, but in the quaint alleyways branching out all around.</p><div class="infobox" style="margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 1.5em; border-radius: 0.5em; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); font-size: 0.8em;"><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28253&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="주소 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Address:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Donggyo-ro 41-gil, Mapo-gu, Seoul</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28259&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="지하철 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Subway:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Line 2, Hongik University Station, Exit 3 (10 mins. on foot)</p></div><div class="horizen" style="margin: 4em 0px; padding: 0px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=22676&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="구분자" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div></div><div class="content" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: center;"><h3 class="hcw_tit" style="margin: 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(252, 184, 238); line-height: 1.3; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">#5 Ansan Jarak-gil<br><span style="display: block; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 10px;">- Editor: Erika (Japan / 10th year in Seoul)<img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28256&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; margin-bottom: 0px; max-width: 100%;"></span></h3><div class="imgbox" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; width: 1000px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28240&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: 1em; max-width: 100%;"></div><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;">Despite being smack dab in the middle of Seoul in Ansan of Seodaemun-gu, Ansan Jarak-gil still remains as a lesser-known hot spot where ongoers retreat for some healing. It begins from behind the Seodaemun-gu District Office building and leads out to the mountainside that makes you feels as if you’ve been transported away from the city, surrounded by the memorizing Spring landscape. The scenery itself makes for a harmonious synergy together with the cherry blossoms bursting with life. You can follow along the path carved out along the mountain for some excellent trekking as well! And at the mountain peak sits the Muak East Beacon Mound (Seoul Monument No. 13), a means of communication used during the Joseon Period, while the observatory offers a bird’s eye view of Inwangsan Mountain across the way, alongside N Seoul Tower and a panoramic capture of Jongno. Take some out of your spring day to come awe at the beauty of the flowing tints and colors marked with yellow and pink notes radiating from the lively crest of forsythias and azaleas brushing the landscape.</p><div class="infobox" style="margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 1.5em; border-radius: 0.5em; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); font-size: 0.8em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28253&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="주소 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Address:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>1 San, Bongwon-dong, Seodaemun-gu, Seoul</p><p style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://www.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=28259&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="지하철 아이콘" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; margin-bottom: -0.6px; max-width: 100%; height: 16px;"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Subway:&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>Line 3, Muakjae Station, Exit 4</p></div><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"><p class="" style="text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; word-break: keep-all; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;">These little gems scattered throughout the city are no easy finds if you haven’t been around! Unfortunately, the call for social distancing amid the recent outbreak has left many of us stranded at home, but that doesn’t mean we can’t jot it down and gear upfor our next opportunity to head outside to enjoy this beautiful spring scenery!</p><div><br></div></div>','9, Yanghwa-ro 6-gil, Mapo-gu, Seoul, Korea','서울 마포구 양화로6길 9',TO_DATE('20/04/27'),TO_DATE('20/04/27'),0,0,'Something new,Famous,Vacation,Calm,Natural','Y','T1','','','','');
EXEC P_THEME_LIST(SEQ_TNO.NEXTVAL,'ADMIN','Breakdown of Korea’s top latenight foods','<p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26475&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Top-leeft:Chicken &amp; Beer,Top-right:Jokbal,Soju,Bottom-left:Jeon,Makegeolli,Bottom-right:Korean Ramen " style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">If you’re planning to travel around Korea, whose latenight snack culture is the most famous among East Asian countries, then you’ll have to sample some delicious latenight foods and snacks that will make your visit all the more special. Ranging from addictively tasty fried chicken, through savory jokbal (pigs’ feet) and deliciously crispy jeon (pan-fried delicacies), to various Korean style ramen (instant noodles), the following are popular food options that you can enjoy the moment you set foot in Korea!</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26483&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h3 class="one" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(227, 127, 33); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">The synergy of the universe!</h3><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Chicken &amp; Beer</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26479&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Chicken &amp; Beer" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Once you’ve sampled the fried chicken in Korea, you’ll never forget the taste. In fact, the No. 1 latenight snack menu ordered by Koreans of all ages is chicken. A dish of crunchy fried chicken washed down with a refreshing glass of cool beer will make you forget all your travel fatigue. Why not experience Korea’s rapid food delivery culture and upload your photo with chicken and beer on your social media page?</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26484&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="2" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h3 class="two" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(111, 65, 57); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Korean soul food best enjoyed with Korean alcohol</h3><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Jokbal &amp; Soju</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26480&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Jokbal &amp; Soju" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Jokbal is a savory dish cooked by boiling pig’s feet in a stock made of herbal medicines, soy sauce and soybean paste. Commonly found in Korea’s traditional markets, its lustrous brown look and soft, delicate taste keeps customers coming back for more. The best way to enjoy it is to take a piece of soft jokbal meat with vegetables such as chives or onions and dip it in ssamjang, a spicy sauce made with soybean paste and red pepper paste. What’s more, if you eat it together with a bottle of soju, Korea’s signature alcohol, you’ll have a truly authentic latenight dining experience! You can choose from traditional jokbal, spicy jokbal, and cold jokbal salad according to your preference.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26485&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="3" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h3 class="three" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(67, 76, 52); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">The true latenight snack food of Korea</h3><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Jeon &amp; Makgeolli</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26481&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Jeon &amp; Makgeolli" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Jeon is a very popular traditional Korean dish that has been loved by Koreans for many years. It resembles a thin pancake that is made by frying dough together with various ingredients such as seafood, vegetables, and kimchi. Jeon is an essential food for Koreans, especially when it rains, as the sound of rain recalls the sound of jeon being cooked. You’ll enjoy your jeon all the more if you have it with makgeolli, an unrefined rice wine made with rice and malt. If you’re sightseeing in Seoul on arainyday, a satisfying snack of jeon and makgeolli is highly recommended!</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26486&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="4" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h3 class="four" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(217, 162, 14); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Like picking candy at a candy store!</h3><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Korean Ramen</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26482&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Korean Ramen" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Although many Asian countries serve different kinds of ramen, Korea boasts the most diverse flavors and kinds of ramen. Whether it’s basic ramen with spicy soup you’re after, or chili-favored stir-fried ramen, or unique ramen products served with a curryorjjajang (black bean sauce) sauce or a simple miyeokguk (seaweed soup), you can buy it easily at a nearby convenience store. Unlike other snacks, you can enjoy cheap, latenight grub easily without having to order it. And with so many to choose from, it might take you while!</p>','173, Garogongwon-ro, Gangseo-gu, Seoul, Korea','서울 강서구 가로공원로 173',TO_DATE('20/04/27'),TO_DATE('20/04/27'),0,0,'Something new,Famous,Tourism,Calm,Urban','Y','T2','','','','');
EXEC P_THEME_LIST(SEQ_TNO.NEXTVAL,'ADMIN','Meet the heroes of the Korean War','"<section class="infor-element" style="margin: 40px auto 0px; padding: 0px; width: 1000px; max-width: 1000px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 16px;"><div class="text-area" style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); word-break: keep-all;"><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24356&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Top-left: War Memorial of Korea, Top-left: Monuments for the Participants, Bottom-left: The War History Room, Bottom-right: The ROK Armed Forces Room" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;"><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">Located in the heart of Seoul is Yongsan, the former site of military headquarters. The War Memorial of Korea is Korea’s one-and-only comprehensive museum, which introduces Korea’s 5,000-year strong history through one theme: “war.” The museum serves not only as an institution for learning, but also as a place to enjoy culture and relaxation.</p><br><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">The War Memorial of Korea has many halls and spaces showcasing the war between North and South Korea, starting from its cause to its development to its ceasefire. It also has zones for visitors to experience war-related programs. Group tours are especially designed to make the content easy to understand.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">Here’s a list of our four recommended courses at the museum!</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><div class="cnt-blockquote" style="margin: 0px; padding: 30px 29px 34px 40px; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); height: auto;"><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><span style="width: 27px; display: inline-block;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24362&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Address" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; margin-top: -3px;"></span><b>Address&nbsp;</b>29 Itaewon-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><span style="width: 27px; display: inline-block;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24366&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Hours" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; margin-top: -3px;"></span><b>Hours&nbsp;</b>Daily 09:30 - 18:00 / Entry until 17:30 (Closed on Mondays)</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><span style="width: 27px; display: inline-block;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24364&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Fee" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; margin-top: -3px;"></span><b>Admission&nbsp;</b>Free (Excluding some special exhibitions)</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><span style="width: 27px; display: inline-block;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24363&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Phone" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; margin-top: -3px;"></span><b>Tel&nbsp;</b>+82-2-709-3139,3114</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><span style="width: 27px; display: inline-block;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24365&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Website" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%; margin-top: -3px;"></span><b>Website&nbsp;</b><span style="color: rgb(2, 125, 195);"><a href="https://www.warmemo.or.kr/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); word-break: break-all;">https://www.warmemo.or.kr</a></span></p></div><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 30px; font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24358&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 25px 0px 24px; font-size: 24px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px;">Educating pre-school &amp; elementary school students</h5><h3 style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3;">History Course for Children</h3><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><img class="main-img2" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24518&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Course 1:Childrens Museum,Course 2: Outdoor Exhibition,Course 3:The War History Room " style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: auto; height: auto; margin: 0px auto; display: block; max-width: 100%;"><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">This course is customized for children between the age of 4 to 10. It starts at Children’s Museum, and leads into the outdoor exhibition area showing war-related equipment, aircrafts, missiles, and then into the War History Room, introducing the war history from the prehistoric times through the Japanese colonial period. Children can have a better understanding of the history and heroes of wars in Korea, as well as experience the courage of Korean ancestors who made great efforts and sacrifices to liberate the country from foreign invasion. The content is made to be easy and fun through a decent program, which is available upon reservation.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><div class="cnt-blockquote" style="margin: 0px; padding: 30px 29px 34px 40px; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); height: auto;"><h6 class="fc blue" style="margin: 0px 0px 18px; padding: 0px 0px 20px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(2, 125, 195);">Children’s Museum Tour Program</h6><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><b>Days&nbsp;</b>Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays &amp; Fridays</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><b>Hours&nbsp;</b>10:00, 11:00, 12:00</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><b>Duration&nbsp;</b>Approx. 30 minutes</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><b>Target&nbsp;</b>Visitors RSVPing for Children’s Museum tour</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); width: 931px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><b>Registration&nbsp;</b>At the museum</p></div><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 30px; font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24359&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="2" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 25px 0px 24px; font-size: 24px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px;">Educating middle &amp; high school students</h5><h3 style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3;">History Course for Teens</h3><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><img class="main-img2" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24522&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Course1:Outdoor Exhibition, Course2:The War History Room,Course3:The Korea War Room I,Course4:The Korea War Room 2,Course5: Emergency Drill Experience Hall" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: auto; height: auto; margin: 0px auto; display: block; max-width: 100%;"><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">This course is customized for middle and high school students, and offers tours throughout various exhibits on the history of war in Korea. The War History Room, displays the timeline of Korean history from the Prehistoric Period, Three Kingdoms Period, North-South States Period, the Goryeo Dynasty, the Joseon Dynasty, the Open-Port period, the Korean Empire, to the Japanese Colonial Period. Students can learn Korean history from the Prehistoric Period before man invented letters through the Japanese colonial rule in the 1910s, as well as stories about the Korean people who strongly resisted and create an independence movement against the brutality of the Japanese and obtained liberation by driven away the Japanese Imperialism. The Korean War Room displays the process of independence in the Korean peninsula and the Korean War. An archive about Kim Il-sung’s preparation for the Korean War can be found as well. The last stop is the Contingency Plan Room where students can learn about contingency plans and experience how to prepare in case of emergency.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 30px; font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24360&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="3" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 25px 0px 24px; font-size: 24px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px;">Educating Korean families</h5><h3 style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3;">History Course for Families</h3><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><img class="main-img2" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24526&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Course1:The War History Room,Course2:The Korea War Room1,Course3:The Korea War Room2,Course4:The Expeditionary Forces Room,Course5: The ROK Armed Forces Room" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: auto; height: auto; margin: 0px auto; display: block; max-width: 100%;"><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">This course is customized for everyday Korean families and it allows them to walk through the Korean War. The Korean War broke out in the early morning of June 25, 1950, when soldiers of the North Korean’s Army poured past the 38th parallel, which was the frontier between the communist North Korea and the pro-democratic South Korea. To the older generation, this war is forever remembered as one of the most painful event in history. The room also includes exhibits on Korea’s great involvement through military dispatch in the Vietnam War, which want to remind us about the importance of peace. The ROK Armed Forces Room, past the symbolic sculpture of Koreans soldiers, is the area that show the history of Korean armed forces. Starting with the time line of the ROK Armed Forces, the room explains the creation of Korean military forces. The course offers a meaningful time for the whole family, who can learn that peace and prosperity, as they know of today, is the very result of effort and sacrifice made by earlier generations.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 30px; font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24361&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="4" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 25px 0px 24px; font-size: 24px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px;">Educating foreign tourists</h5><h3 style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.375em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; line-height: 1.3;">History Course for Foreigners</h3><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><img class="main-img2" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=24530&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Course1:Monuments for the Participants,Course2:Monuments for role of honor,Course3: The Korea War Room I1,Course4: The Korea War Room I,Course5: UN Room, Course6: The Expeditionary Forces Room" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: auto; height: auto; margin: 0px auto; display: block; max-width: 100%;"><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6;">This course is customized for foreign people interested in Korean history and it starts with at the outdoor Peace Plaza. There is a monument commemorating the participation of different countries and includes commemorative words of gratitude to all the participating countries writing in the Korean language and the language of the corresponding country. It also honors the role of military soldiers and police officers killed in action during the Korean War. The Republic of Korea established its official governmenton August 15, 1948 in accordance to the ONU procedure. On September 9, 1948, Kim Il-sung of North Korea started a new nation under the name Democratic Popular Republic of Korea. From these events, two separate governments were born in the Korean peninsula.However, the former leader of North Korea started a civil war to unify the peninsula under one communist regime. The Korean War Room tells that stories in detail, from the process of national independence in the Korean peninsula to the preparations of war made by Kim Il-sung.</p></div></section><section class="tag-element detail" style="margin: 10px auto 40px; padding: 40px 0px; width: 1200px; max-width: 1200px; position: relative; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 16px;"><span class="title" style="display: block; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 102, 235); font-weight: 700; padding-left: 25px; background-image: url(&quot;../../../assets/images/2019/common/ico-tag.png&quot;); background-position: 0px 3px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; padding-right: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tags</span></section>"','29, Itaewon-ro, Yongsan-gu, Seoul, Korea','서울 용산구 이태원로 29',TO_DATE('20/04/27'),TO_DATE('20/04/27'),0,0,'Something new,Famous,Tourism,Calm,Urban','Y','T3','','','','');
EXEC P_THEME_LIST(SEQ_TNO.NEXTVAL,'ADMIN','Age-old, traditional alcohol','<p><br></p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26969&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Time-Honored ‘Traditional Korean Alcoholic Drinks’" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">These days, the most common alcoholic drinks in Korea are soju (a clear, colorless distilled beverage) and beer. However, Korea boasts traditional alcohol as good as any famous alcohol in the world. Korea has a long history and traditions for crafting alcohol. Recently, traditional Korean alcohol has been markedly developed, gaining wider popularity among the public while keeping their pride as a national heritage. Let’s learn dig a little deeper below!</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26977&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="1" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Overview</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26973&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Traditional Alcohol" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Korea boasts hundreds of kinds of traditional alcohol. Each region has its own drinks. Recipes are endlessly diverse. Traditional Korean alcohol can be divided into fermented liquors and distilled liquors. Brewed liquors are made from grains and fruits through a fermentation process. Thus they are called fermented liquors, too. Makgeolli (rice wine) is the most popular fermented alcohol in Korea, with a lower alcohol content than distilled liquors. Distilled liquors are madeby distilling fermented liquors in a distiller. To obtain a spirit of higher purity, distilling involves boiling and cooling processes. Traditional Korean distilled liquors include maesilju and bokbunjaju made from fruit.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26978&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="2" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">History</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26974&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Left: Traditional Alcohol, Right: Brewery" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">With a long history involved, Korea has traditional alcoholic beverages of numerous kinds and tastes. During the Joseon Dynasty, men liked to drink at dinner, leading to the development of various kinds of beverages. As part of their cultural annihilationpolicy,Japanese colonizers banned ordinary people from making alcohol except in licensed breweries. Our traditional brewing discontinued altogether. In 1995, making alcoholic beverages in our traditional way was allowed by the government. The culture of brewing traditional liquors was reinvented. Here are some outstanding places that have been trying to foster such a valuable cultural heritage.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="padding-bottom: 12px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: center; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;"><img src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26979&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="3" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 100%;"></p><h5 style="margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px 20px; font-size: 32px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-align: center; width: 1000px; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Brew Your Own Liquor – Samhae Soju Brewery</h5><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p><img class="main-img" src="http://english.visitseoul.net/comm/getImage?srvcId=MEDIA&amp;parentSn=26975&amp;fileTy=MEDIA&amp;fileNo=1" alt="Samhae Soju Brewery" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: middle; width: 1000px; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"></p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><p class="" style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">Samhae Soju Brewery is run by Kim Taek-sang who is a master craftsman designated by the Seoul Metropolitan Government as an intangible cultural heritage. With an alcohol content of 45 percent, Samhae Soju was a high-end liquor consumed by the ruling class during the Joseon Dynasty. Having revived the invaluable brewing technique, Kim Taek-sang has run the place for 15 years to introduce the liquor that was rarely available to the public during the dynasty. Make a reservation to attend a lecture and atastingsession.You can also participate in the liquor-making process through a separate application process.</p><p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); width: 1000px; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 2px; line-height: 1.6; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;;">&nbsp;</p><div class="cnt-blockquote" style="margin: 0px; padding: 20px 30px; background: rgb(245, 245, 245); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); height: auto; font-family: &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, Arial, &quot;Nanum Barun Gothic&quot;, &quot;맑은 고딕&quot;, &quot;Malgun Gothic&quot;; font-size: 17px;"><h6 class="fc blue" style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(2, 125, 195);">Samhae Soju Brewery</h6><div style="margin: 0px 0px 6px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; display: inline-block; width: 940px; line-height: 1;"><div class="title-wrap" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 130px;"